Lack of context

The misclassification primarily stems from
 Absence of counterfactual examples demonstrating how recurrence versus new onset qualifies as developed disorder per diagnostic frameworks
 Missing clinical interpretation of symptom fluctuations eg

whether T severity represented active disorder or residual symptoms
 Insufficient context regarding diagnostic thresholds for development including relapse criteria in longitudinal assessment
